<subSubSection id="C37416F0F455FFA8FF5069E65A22F957" pageId="10" pageNumber="137" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BD1457BF455FFA8FF5069E65BB1FF43" blockId="10.[136,230,194,220]" box="[136,230,194,220]" pageId="10" pageNumber="137">
<figureCitation id="135559FEF455FFA8FF5069E65BB1FF43" box="[136,230,194,220]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="10.[136,229,1318,1340]" captionTargetBox="[157,1423,498,1283]" captionTargetId="figure-120@10.[151,1436,494,1290]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 9. Puccinia polysora on Zea mays (TA401). A Epiphyllous uredinia B urediniospores drawn in optical sections except one spore C apical parts of paraphyses. Scale bars: 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6597627" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6597627/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="137">Figure 9</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD1457BF455FFA8FF50682D5952FE47" blockId="10.[136,1451,265,472]" pageId="10" pageNumber="137">
<emphasis id="B91A9969F455FFA8FF50682D5BA6FEBC" bold="true" box="[136,241,265,291]" pageId="10" pageNumber="137">Uredinia</emphasis>
amphigenous, sparse, mostly elongated or oval, 
<quantity id="4C96E89EF455FFA8FCF0682E58DFFEBB" box="[808,904,266,292]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="137" unit="mm" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2–3 mm</quantity>
long, subepidermal, erumpent. 
<emphasis id="B91A9969F455FFA8FB2E682D5EFCFEBC" bold="true" box="[1270,1451,265,291]" pageId="10" pageNumber="137">Urediniospores</emphasis>
mostly ellipsoidal to oblong or globose, sometimes broadly ellipsoidal, rarely cylindrical, (23–)28–35(–38) × (18–)21–24(–29) µm (n = 120), brown to golden brown, echinulate, spines 1.5–2 µm long, wall 1–2 µm thick, with 2 or 3 equatorial germ pores. 
<emphasis id="B91A9969F455FFA8FE5468525942FE0F" bold="true" box="[396,533,374,400]" pageId="10" pageNumber="137">Paraphyses</emphasis>
cylindrical, spatula-shaped, or slightly curved, rounded and sometimes thicker at the tip, (33–)40–52(–55) × (5–)6–9(–10) µm (n = 15, width measured in the middle of the paraphyses), hyaline, wall 1–2 µm thick. 
<emphasis id="B91A9969F455FFA8FEF468995A31FE48" bold="true" box="[300,358,445,471]" pageId="10" pageNumber="137">Telia</emphasis>
not observed.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF1115F3F455FFA8FF506C02590FFAC0" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6597627" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6597627" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6597627/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="137" startId="10.[136,229,1318,1340]" targetBox="[157,1423,498,1283]" targetPageId="10">
<paragraph id="8BD1457BF455FFA8FF506C02590FFAC0" blockId="10.[136,1451,1318,1376]" pageId="10" pageNumber="137">
<emphasis id="B91A9969F455FFA8FF506C025BAAFAA4" bold="true" box="[136,253,1318,1340]" pageId="10" pageNumber="137">FIGURE 9.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C6E3EF8F455FFA8FEDA6C025AE7FAA4" box="[258,432,1318,1339]" class="Pucciniomycetes" family="Pucciniaceae" genus="Puccinia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pucciniales" pageId="10" pageNumber="137" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="polysora">
<emphasis id="B91A9969F455FFA8FEDA6C025AE7FAA4" box="[258,432,1318,1339]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="137">Puccinia polysora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on 
<taxonomicName id="4C6E3EF8F455FFA8FE0A6C03597BFAA3" box="[466,556,1319,1340]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Zea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="10" pageNumber="137" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mays">
<emphasis id="B91A9969F455FFA8FE0A6C03597BFAA3" box="[466,556,1319,1340]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="137">Zea mays</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(TA401). 
<emphasis id="B91A9969F455FFA8FD576C0259F7FAA4" bold="true" box="[655,672,1318,1339]" pageId="10" pageNumber="137">A</emphasis>
Epiphyllous uredinia 
<emphasis id="B91A9969F455FFA8FCAA6C0258D5FAA4" bold="true" box="[882,898,1318,1339]" pageId="10" pageNumber="137">B</emphasis>
urediniospores drawn in optical sections except one spore 
<emphasis id="B91A9969F455FFA8FF506C6E5BCEFAFF" bold="true" box="[136,153,1354,1376]" pageId="10" pageNumber="137">C</emphasis>
apical parts of paraphyses. Scale bars: 10 µm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BD1457BF455FFA8FF656CAA5FCCFA53" blockId="10.[136,1452,1422,2025]" pageId="10" pageNumber="137">
28S rDNA sequences from 
<specimenCount id="9D688EF2F455FFA8FE276CAB59FFFA37" box="[511,680,1422,1449]" pageId="10" pageNumber="137" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
